The paper focuses on visualizing the decision-making process of a deep neural decision forest (NDF) model for various vision tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper combines decision tree and deep representation learning, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the distribution of routing probabilities, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
